The paint is scratched in spots from being used, but over all this is a great truck that has never failed me. I am the original owner and bought it new from a dealer in Georgia. If you are looking for a great work truck, Hunting truck, etc.. this is perfect. I have used this as my everyday driving vehicle.

A six position telescoping buttstock offers light weight, carrying ease and quick handling. 

The telestock, pistol grip and two piece handguards are all molded of strong black thermoset composite material. The handguards are internally shielded against barrel heat build-up. The dual aperture M16A2 rear sight system on these carbines offer both windage and elevation adjustment calibrated in meters. 

The A3 Type Patrolmans Carbine includes a Removable Carry Handle - adjustment range is from from 300 to 600 meters (1/2 M.o.A. elevation and 1/2 M.o.A. windage).

Once the Carry Handle is removed, a wide variety of scopes, red dot or holographic sights, or night vision equipment may be mounted on the Upper Receivers integral Picatinny rail. Iron sight zero is completely repeatable when the handle is reattached by means of its knurled knobs. 

The Bushmaster A2/A3 Type Patrolmans Carbines are shipped complete with 30 round magazine, safety and operational manual, and carry sling.

For sale is a Sig Sauer P239 SAS Gen 2 pistol.  The P239 is well suited for concealed carry or use as a backup gun.  It is a Single Action/Double Action with a de-cocking lever.  The SAS Gen 2 designation means that this weapon was upgraded by the Sig custom shop.  The changes made involve rounding the square/sharp edges (dehorning) of the P239 so that the pistol wont catch on clothing, etc when used for concealed carry.  This gun is chambered for 357 Sig, which makes it an excellent bad-guy stopper.  It is equipped with factory night sights and they still glow bright.  In addition to the 2-7 round mags included with the pistol I purchased and am including 3-8 round extended mags.  I also purchased a snappy leather holster for it that is included as well. this rare German Makarov is chambered for the 9mm Makarov, which is ballistically between the .380 and the 9mm Luger. It was produced by the historic Suhl factory which fell into Russian hands after the "iron curtain" came down. East German firearms are unheard of except for a few VOPO (People's Police) Lugers and this standardized 9mm Makarov. The finish is excellent dark blue with extra magazine and original holster. This was made in a country that does not exist any more. After the Wall came down a small amount of these trickled in until surplus EG weapons were given to the variou sides in the Balkan Civil War.
